
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `browse` (ya `xdg-open` dar aksar system-ha) baraye baz kardane file-ha ya URL-ha ba barnameye pishfarz (default) estefade mishavad. In dastoor otomatik mifahmad che barnamei baraye baz kardane file ya URL bayad estefade shavad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `browse <file>` --> 📂 Baz kardane yek file ba barnameye pishfarz.
    🔹 `browse <URL>`  --> 🌐 Baz kardane yek URL dar browser-e pishfarz.
    🔹 `xdg-open <file>`  --> 📂 Equivalent command to open a file with the default application (in many systems).
    🔹 `xdg-open <URL>`   --> 🌐 Equivalent command to open a URL in the default browser (in many systems).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ browse document.pdf

    🔹 Baz kardane file "document.pdf" ba barnameye pishfarz baraye PDF.

    $ browse https://www.example.com

    🔹 Baz kardane website "https://www.example.com" dar browser-e pishfarz.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ browse image.jpg

    🔹 File "image.jpg" ba barnameye pishfarze tasvir baz mishavad. Agar barnameye pishfarze tasvir Mojod nabashad, system az shoma mikhad ke yek barname entekhab konid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `browse` command (or `xdg-open` in many systems) is used to open files or URLs with the default application. It automatically detects which application to use based on the file type or URL.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `browse <file>` --> 📂 Open a file with the default application.
    🔹 `browse <URL>`  --> 🌐 Open a URL in the default browser.
    🔹 `xdg-open <file>`  --> 📂 Equivalent command to open a file with the default application (in many systems).
    🔹 `xdg-open <URL>`   --> 🌐 Equivalent command to open a URL in the default browser (in many systems).

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ browse document.pdf

    🔹 Opens the "document.pdf" file with the default PDF viewer.

    $ browse https://www.example.com

    🔹 Opens the website "https://www.example.com" in the default web browser.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ browse image.jpg

    🔹 The "image.jpg" file will be opened with the default image viewer. If no default image viewer is configured, the system might prompt you to select one.
